When Cursor auto-generates a Git commit message (sparkle button in Source Control), follow these rules:

1. Use Conventional Commits: `<type>: <description>` or `<type>(<scope>): <description>`
2. Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore, ci, build
3. Subject line MUST be 100 characters or fewer (count the entire line)
4. Lowercase type and description; no period at the end
5. Single line only — no body or footer
6. Be specific and concise about what changed

Examples:
- feat: add waveform trimming UI
- fix(audio): resolve playback crash on seek
- chore: update expo dependencies
